definition: tree/wood/coffin/wooden/simple/numb/one of the eight categories of ancient musical instruments 八音[ba1 yin1]

to take care (of)/to control/to manage/to be in charge of/to look after/to run/to care about/tube/pipe/woodwind/classifier for tube-shaped objects/particle similar to 把[ba3] in 管...叫 constructions/writing brush/(coll.) to/towards

sentences.english: Cor Anglais belongs to woodwind section.
Originally, flute is belong to woodwind, later made by metal.
sentences.chinese: 長笛原來屬於木管樂器，後來改用金屬製造。

sentences.english: He won first prize in the woodwind section.
sentences.chinese: 他獲得木管樂器組一等獎。

sentences.english: The most common woodwinds are the reed instruments.
sentences.chinese: 最常見的木管樂器是簧片樂器。

sentences.english: I need a single-reed woodwind with a conical bore.
sentences.chinese: 我需要帶有一個圓錐孔的單簧木管樂器。
